						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab from the Īśvara temple at Madarkhaṇḍi, now kept in the house of Mr. W.T. Apte.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa—(Date lost).</p>						

						<p>No details of the date except <hi rend="bold">Śrāvaṇa, ba. Tuesday</hi> are preserved in this fragmentary record.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a grant of oil for some religious purpose, in the presence of the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> who assembled in the <hi rend="italic">Sabhāmaṇṭapa</hi> for the purpose.</p>						

						</summary>
